  29 def assert_dtype(obj, expected_dtype):
  30     """
  31     Helper to check the dtype for a Series, Index, or single-column DataFrame.
  32     """
  33     if isinstance(obj, DataFrame):
  34         dtype = obj.dtypes.iat[0]
  35     else:
  36         dtype = obj.dtype
  37 
  38     assert dtype == expected_dtype

  45 class TestTimedelta64ArrayLikeComparisons:
  46     # Comparison tests for timedelta64[ns] vectors fully parametrized over
  47     #  DataFrame/Series/TimedeltaIndex/TimedeltaArray.  Ideally all comparison
  48     #  tests will eventually end up here.
  49 
  50     def test_compare_timedelta64_zerodim(self, box_with_array):
  51         # GH#26689 should unbox when comparing with zerodim array
  52         box = box_with_array
  53         xbox = box_with_array if box_with_array is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
  54 
  55         tdi = pd.timedelta_range("2H", periods=4)
  56         other = np.array(tdi.to_numpy()[0])
  57 
  58         tdi = tm.box_expected(tdi, box)
  59         res = tdi <= other
  60         expected = np.array([True, False, False, False])
  61         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
  62         tm.assert_equal(res, expected)
  63 
  64         msg = "Invalid comparison between dtype"
  65         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
  66             # zero-dim of wrong dtype should still raise
  67             tdi >= np.array(4)
  68 
  69     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
  70         "td_scalar",
  71         [timedelta(days=1), Timedelta(days=1), Timedelta(days=1).to_timedelta64()],
  72     )
  73     def test_compare_timedeltalike_scalar(self, box_with_array, td_scalar):
  74         # regression test for GH#5963
  75         box = box_with_array
  76         xbox = box if box is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
  77         ser = pd.Series([timedelta(days=1), timedelta(days=2)])
  78         ser = tm.box_expected(ser, box)
  79         actual = ser > td_scalar
  80         expected = pd.Series([False, True])
  81         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
  82         tm.assert_equal(actual, expected)
  83 
  84     @pytest.mark.parametrize("invalid", [345600000000000, "a"])
  85     def test_td64_comparisons_invalid(self, box_with_array, invalid):
  86         # GH#13624 for str
  87         box = box_with_array
  88         rng = timedelta_range("1 days", periods=10)
  89         obj = tm.box_expected(rng, box)
  90 
  91         assert_invalid_comparison(obj, invalid, box)

  93     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
  94         "other",
  95         [
  96             list(range(10)),
  97             np.arange(10),
  98             np.arange(10).astype(np.float32),
  99             np.arange(10).astype(object),
 100             pd.date_range("1970-01-01", periods=10, tz="UTC").array,
 101             np.array(pd.date_range("1970-01-01", periods=10)),
 102             list(pd.date_range("1970-01-01", periods=10)),
 103             pd.date_range("1970-01-01", periods=10).astype(object),
 104             pd.period_range("1971-01-01", freq="D", periods=10).array,
 105             pd.period_range("1971-01-01", freq="D", periods=10).astype(object),
 106         ],
 107     )
 108     def test_td64arr_cmp_arraylike_invalid(self, other):
 109         # We don't parametrize this over box_with_array because listlike
 110         #  other plays poorly with assert_invalid_comparison reversed checks
 111 
 112         rng = timedelta_range("1 days", periods=10)._data
 113         assert_invalid_comparison(rng, other, tm.to_array)
 114 
 115     def test_td64arr_cmp_mixed_invalid(self):
 116         rng = timedelta_range("1 days", periods=5)._data
 117 
 118         other = np.array([0, 1, 2, rng[3], pd.Timestamp.now()])
 119         result = rng == other
 120         expected = np.array([False, False, False, True, False])
 121         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 122 
 123         result = rng != other
 124         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, ~expected)
 125 
 126         msg = "Invalid comparison between|Cannot compare type|not supported between"
 127         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 128             rng < other
 129         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 130             rng > other
 131         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 132             rng <= other
 133         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 134             rng >= other

 140     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype", [None, object])
 141     def test_comp_nat(self, dtype):
 142         left = pd.TimedeltaIndex(
 143             [pd.Timedelta("1 days"), pd.NaT, pd.Timedelta("3 days")]
 144         )
 145         right = pd.TimedeltaIndex([pd.NaT, pd.NaT, pd.Timedelta("3 days")])
 146 
 147         lhs, rhs = left, right
 148         if dtype is object:
 149             lhs, rhs = left.astype(object), right.astype(object)
 150 
 151         result = rhs == lhs
 152         expected = np.array([False, False, True])
 153         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 154 
 155         result = rhs != lhs
 156         expected = np.array([True, True, False])
 157         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 158 
 159         expected = np.array([False, False, False])
 160         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(lhs == pd.NaT, expected)
 161         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(pd.NaT == rhs, expected)
 162 
 163         expected = np.array([True, True, True])
 164         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(lhs != pd.NaT, expected)
 165         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(pd.NaT != lhs, expected)
 166 
 167         expected = np.array([False, False, False])
 168         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(lhs < pd.NaT, expected)
 169         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(pd.NaT > lhs, expected)
 170 
 171     def test_comparisons_nat(self):
 172         tdidx1 = pd.TimedeltaIndex(
 173             [
 174                 "1 day",
 175                 pd.NaT,
 176                 "1 day 00:00:01",
 177                 pd.NaT,
 178                 "1 day 00:00:01",
 179                 "5 day 00:00:03",
 180             ]
 181         )
 182         tdidx2 = pd.TimedeltaIndex(
 183             ["2 day", "2 day", pd.NaT, pd.NaT, "1 day 00:00:02", "5 days 00:00:03"]
 184         )
 185         tdarr = np.array(
 186             [
 187                 np.timedelta64(2, "D"),
 188                 np.timedelta64(2, "D"),
 189                 np.timedelta64("nat"),
 190                 np.timedelta64("nat"),
 191                 np.timedelta64(1, "D") + np.timedelta64(2, "s"),
 192                 np.timedelta64(5, "D") + np.timedelta64(3, "s"),
 193             ]
 194         )
 195 
 196         cases = [(tdidx1, tdidx2), (tdidx1, tdarr)]
 197 
 198         # Check pd.NaT is handles as the same as np.nan
 199         for idx1, idx2 in cases:
 200 
 201             result = idx1 < idx2
 202             expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, False])
 203             tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 204 
 205             result = idx2 > idx1
 206             expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, False])
 207             tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 208 
 209             result = idx1 <= idx2
 210             expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, True])
 211             tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 212 
 213             result = idx2 >= idx1
 214             expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, True])
 215             tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 216 
 217             result = idx1 == idx2
 218             expected = np.array([False, False, False, False, False, True])
 219             tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 220 
 221             result = idx1 != idx2
 222             expected = np.array([True, True, True, True, True, False])
 223             tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 224 
 225     # TODO: better name
 226     def test_comparisons_coverage(self):
 227         rng = timedelta_range("1 days", periods=10)
 228 
 229         result = rng < rng[3]
 230         expected = np.array([True, True, True] + [False] * 7)
 231         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 232 
 233         result = rng == list(rng)
 234         exp = rng == rng
 235         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, exp)

 246     def test_ufunc_coercions(self):
 247         # normal ops are also tested in tseries/test_timedeltas.py
 248         idx = TimedeltaIndex(["2H", "4H", "6H", "8H", "10H"], freq="2H", name="x")
 249 
 250         for result in [idx * 2, np.multiply(idx, 2)]:
 251             assert isinstance(result, TimedeltaIndex)
 252             exp = TimedeltaIndex(["4H", "8H", "12H", "16H", "20H"], freq="4H", name="x")
 253             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 254             assert result.freq == "4H"
 255 
 256         for result in [idx / 2, np.divide(idx, 2)]:
 257             assert isinstance(result, TimedeltaIndex)
 258             exp = TimedeltaIndex(["1H", "2H", "3H", "4H", "5H"], freq="H", name="x")
 259             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 260             assert result.freq == "H"
 261 
 262         idx = TimedeltaIndex(["2H", "4H", "6H", "8H", "10H"], freq="2H", name="x")
 263         for result in [-idx, np.negative(idx)]:
 264             assert isinstance(result, TimedeltaIndex)
 265             exp = TimedeltaIndex(
 266                 ["-2H", "-4H", "-6H", "-8H", "-10H"], freq="-2H", name="x"
 267             )
 268             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 269             assert result.freq == "-2H"
 270 
 271         idx = TimedeltaIndex(["-2H", "-1H", "0H", "1H", "2H"], freq="H", name="x")
 272         for result in [abs(idx), np.absolute(idx)]:
 273             assert isinstance(result, TimedeltaIndex)
 274             exp = TimedeltaIndex(["2H", "1H", "0H", "1H", "2H"], freq=None, name="x")
 275             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 276             assert result.freq is None
 277 
 278     def test_subtraction_ops(self):
 279         # with datetimes/timedelta and tdi/dti
 280         tdi = TimedeltaIndex(["1 days", pd.NaT, "2 days"], name="foo")
 281         dti = pd.date_range("20130101", periods=3, name="bar")
 282         td = Timedelta("1 days")
 283         dt = Timestamp("20130101")
 284 
 285         msg = "cannot subtract a datelike from a TimedeltaArray"
 286         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 287             tdi - dt
 288         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 289             tdi - dti
 290 
 291         msg = r"unsupported operand type\(s\) for -"
 292         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 293             td - dt
 294 
 295         msg = "(bad|unsupported) operand type for unary"
 296         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 297             td - dti
 298 
 299         result = dt - dti
 300         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", "-1 days", "-2 days"], name="bar")
 301         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 302 
 303         result = dti - dt
 304         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", "1 days", "2 days"], name="bar")
 305         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 306 
 307         result = tdi - td
 308         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", pd.NaT, "1 days"], name="foo")
 309         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected, check_names=False)
 310 
 311         result = td - tdi
 312         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", pd.NaT, "-1 days"], name="foo")
 313         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected, check_names=False)
 314 
 315         result = dti - td
 316         expected = DatetimeIndex(
 317             ["20121231", "20130101", "20130102"], freq="D", name="bar"
 318         )
 319         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected, check_names=False)
 320 
 321         result = dt - tdi
 322         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20121231", pd.NaT, "20121230"], name="foo")
 323         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 324 
 325     def test_subtraction_ops_with_tz(self):
 326 
 327         # check that dt/dti subtraction ops with tz are validated
 328         dti = pd.date_range("20130101", periods=3)
 329         ts = Timestamp("20130101")
 330         dt = ts.to_pydatetime()
 331         dti_tz = pd.date_range("20130101", periods=3).tz_localize("US/Eastern")
 332         ts_tz = Timestamp("20130101").tz_localize("US/Eastern")
 333         ts_tz2 = Timestamp("20130101").tz_localize("CET")
 334         dt_tz = ts_tz.to_pydatetime()
 335         td = Timedelta("1 days")
 336 
 337         def _check(result, expected):
 338             assert result == expected
 339             assert isinstance(result, Timedelta)
 340 
 341         # scalars
 342         result = ts - ts
 343         expected = Timedelta("0 days")
 344         _check(result, expected)
 345 
 346         result = dt_tz - ts_tz
 347         expected = Timedelta("0 days")
 348         _check(result, expected)
 349 
 350         result = ts_tz - dt_tz
 351         expected = Timedelta("0 days")
 352         _check(result, expected)
 353 
 354         # tz mismatches
 355         msg = "Timestamp subtraction must have the same timezones or no timezones"
 356         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 357             dt_tz - ts
 358         msg = "can't subtract offset-naive and offset-aware datetimes"
 359         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 360             dt_tz - dt
 361         msg = "Timestamp subtraction must have the same timezones or no timezones"
 362         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 363             dt_tz - ts_tz2
 364         msg = "can't subtract offset-naive and offset-aware datetimes"
 365         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 366             dt - dt_tz
 367         msg = "Timestamp subtraction must have the same timezones or no timezones"
 368         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 369             ts - dt_tz
 370         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 371             ts_tz2 - ts
 372         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 373             ts_tz2 - dt
 374         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 375             ts_tz - ts_tz2
 376 
 377         # with dti
 378         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 379             dti - ts_tz
 380         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 381             dti_tz - ts
 382         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 383             dti_tz - ts_tz2
 384 
 385         result = dti_tz - dt_tz
 386         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", "1 days", "2 days"])
 387         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 388 
 389         result = dt_tz - dti_tz
 390         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", "-1 days", "-2 days"])
 391         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 392 
 393         result = dti_tz - ts_tz
 394         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", "1 days", "2 days"])
 395         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 396 
 397         result = ts_tz - dti_tz
 398         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", "-1 days", "-2 days"])
 399         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 400 
 401         result = td - td
 402         expected = Timedelta("0 days")
 403         _check(result, expected)
 404 
 405         result = dti_tz - td
 406         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20121231", "20130101", "20130102"], tz="US/Eastern")
 407         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 408 
 409     def test_dti_tdi_numeric_ops(self):
 410         # These are normally union/diff set-like ops
 411         tdi = TimedeltaIndex(["1 days", pd.NaT, "2 days"], name="foo")
 412         dti = pd.date_range("20130101", periods=3, name="bar")
 413 
 414         # TODO(wesm): unused?
 415         # td = Timedelta('1 days')
 416         # dt = Timestamp('20130101')
 417 
 418         result = tdi - tdi
 419         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["0 days", pd.NaT, "0 days"], name="foo")
 420         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 421 
 422         result = tdi + tdi
 423         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["2 days", pd.NaT, "4 days"], name="foo")
 424         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 425 
 426         result = dti - tdi  # name will be reset
 427         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20121231", pd.NaT, "20130101"])
 428         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)

 430     def test_addition_ops(self):
 431         # with datetimes/timedelta and tdi/dti
 432         tdi = TimedeltaIndex(["1 days", pd.NaT, "2 days"], name="foo")
 433         dti = pd.date_range("20130101", periods=3, name="bar")
 434         td = Timedelta("1 days")
 435         dt = Timestamp("20130101")
 436 
 437         result = tdi + dt
 438         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20130102", pd.NaT, "20130103"], name="foo")
 439         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 440 
 441         result = dt + tdi
 442         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20130102", pd.NaT, "20130103"], name="foo")
 443         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 444 
 445         result = td + tdi
 446         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["2 days", pd.NaT, "3 days"], name="foo")
 447         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 448 
 449         result = tdi + td
 450         expected = TimedeltaIndex(["2 days", pd.NaT, "3 days"], name="foo")
 451         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 452 
 453         # unequal length
 454         msg = "cannot add indices of unequal length"
 455         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 456             tdi + dti[0:1]
 457         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 458             tdi[0:1] + dti
 459 
 460         # random indexes
 461         msg = "Addition/subtraction of integers and integer-arrays"
 462         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 463             tdi + pd.Int64Index([1, 2, 3])
 464 
 465         # this is a union!
 466         # pytest.raises(TypeError, lambda : Int64Index([1,2,3]) + tdi)
 467 
 468         result = tdi + dti  # name will be reset
 469         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20130102", pd.NaT, "20130105"])
 470         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 471 
 472         result = dti + tdi  # name will be reset
 473         expected = DatetimeIndex(["20130102", pd.NaT, "20130105"])
 474         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 475 
 476         result = dt + td
 477         expected = Timestamp("20130102")
 478         assert result == expected
 479 
 480         result = td + dt
 481         expected = Timestamp("20130102")
 482         assert result == expected
 483 
 484     # TODO: Needs more informative name, probably split up into
 485     # more targeted tests
 486     @pytest.mark.parametrize("freq", ["D", "B"])
 487     def test_timedelta(self, freq):
 488         index = pd.date_range("1/1/2000", periods=50, freq=freq)
 489 
 490         shifted = index + timedelta(1)
 491         back = shifted + timedelta(-1)
 492         back = back._with_freq("infer")
 493         tm.assert_index_equal(index, back)
 494 
 495         if freq == "D":
 496             expected = pd.tseries.offsets.Day(1)
 497             assert index.freq == expected
 498             assert shifted.freq == expected
 499             assert back.freq == expected
 500         else:  # freq == 'B'
 501             assert index.freq == pd.tseries.offsets.BusinessDay(1)
 502             assert shifted.freq is None
 503             assert back.freq == pd.tseries.offsets.BusinessDay(1)
 504 
 505         result = index - timedelta(1)
 506         expected = index + timedelta(-1)
 507         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 508 
 509         # GH#4134, buggy with timedeltas
 510         rng = pd.date_range("2013", "2014")
 511         s = Series(rng)
 512         result1 = rng - pd.offsets.Hour(1)
 513         result2 = DatetimeIndex(s - np.timedelta64(100000000))
 514         result3 = rng - np.timedelta64(100000000)
 515         result4 = DatetimeIndex(s - pd.offsets.Hour(1))
 516 
 517         assert result1.freq == rng.freq
 518         result1 = result1._with_freq(None)
 519         tm.assert_index_equal(result1, result4)
 520 
 521         assert result3.freq == rng.freq
 522         result3 = result3._with_freq(None)
 523         tm.assert_index_equal(result2, result3)
 524

 537         expected = tdi + tdi
 538         tm.assert_index_equal(result, expected)
 539

 541         expected = tdi - tdi

 597     def test_tdi_ops_attributes(self):
 598         rng = timedelta_range("2 days", periods=5, freq="2D", name="x")
 599 
 600         result = rng + 1 * rng.freq
 601         exp = timedelta_range("4 days", periods=5, freq="2D", name="x")
 602         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 603         assert result.freq == "2D"
 604 
 605         result = rng - 2 * rng.freq
 606         exp = timedelta_range("-2 days", periods=5, freq="2D", name="x")
 607         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 608         assert result.freq == "2D"
 609 
 610         result = rng * 2
 611         exp = timedelta_range("4 days", periods=5, freq="4D", name="x")
 612         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 613         assert result.freq == "4D"
 614 
 615         result = rng / 2
 616         exp = timedelta_range("1 days", periods=5, freq="D", name="x")
 617         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 618         assert result.freq == "D"
 619 
 620         result = -rng
 621         exp = timedelta_range("-2 days", periods=5, freq="-2D", name="x")
 622         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 623         assert result.freq == "-2D"
 624 
 625         rng = pd.timedelta_range("-2 days", periods=5, freq="D", name="x")
 626 
 627         result = abs(rng)
 628         exp = TimedeltaIndex(
 629             ["2 days", "1 days", "0 days", "1 days", "2 days"], name="x"
 630         )
 631         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 632         assert result.freq is None

 638     def test_tdi_add_timestamp_nat_masking(self):
 639         # GH#17991 checking for overflow-masking with NaT

 662     def test_tdi_add_overflow(self):
 663         # See GH#14068
 664         # preliminary test scalar analogue of vectorized tests below
 665         # TODO: Make raised error message more informative and test
 666         with pytest.raises(OutOfBoundsDatetime, match="10155196800000000000"):
 667             pd.to_timedelta(106580, "D") + Timestamp("2000")
 668         with pytest.raises(OutOfBoundsDatetime, match="10155196800000000000"):
 669             Timestamp("2000") + pd.to_timedelta(106580, "D")
 670 
 671         _NaT = int(pd.NaT) + 1
 672         msg = "Overflow in int64 addition"
 673         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
 674             pd.to_timedelta([106580], "D") + Timestamp("2000")
 675         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
 676             Timestamp("2000") + pd.to_timedelta([106580], "D")
 677         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
 678             pd.to_timedelta([_NaT]) - Timedelta("1 days")
 679         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
 680             pd.to_timedelta(["5 days", _NaT]) - Timedelta("1 days")
 681         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
 682             (
 683                 pd.to_timedelta([_NaT, "5 days", "1 hours"])
 684                 - pd.to_timedelta(["7 seconds", _NaT, "4 hours"])
 685             )
 686 
 687         # These should not overflow!
 688         exp = TimedeltaIndex([pd.NaT])
 689         result = pd.to_timedelta([pd.NaT]) - Timedelta("1 days")
 690         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 691 
 692         exp = TimedeltaIndex(["4 days", pd.NaT])
 693         result = pd.to_timedelta(["5 days", pd.NaT]) - Timedelta("1 days")
 694         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
 695 
 696         exp = TimedeltaIndex([pd.NaT, pd.NaT, "5 hours"])
 697         result = pd.to_timedelta([pd.NaT, "5 days", "1 hours"]) + pd.to_timedelta(
 698             ["7 seconds", pd.NaT, "4 hours"]
 699         )
 700         tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)

 706     # TODO: moved from tests.indexes.timedeltas.test_arithmetic; needs
 707     #  parametrization+de-duplication
 708     def test_timedelta_ops_with_missing_values(self):
 709         # setup
 710         s1 = pd.to_timedelta(Series(["00:00:01"]))
 711         s2 = pd.to_timedelta(Series(["00:00:02"]))
 712 
 713         msg = r"dtype datetime64\[ns\] cannot be converted to timedelta64\[ns\]"
 714         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 715             # Passing datetime64-dtype data to TimedeltaIndex is no longer
 716             #  supported GH#29794
 717             pd.to_timedelta(Series([pd.NaT]))
 718 
 719         sn = pd.to_timedelta(Series([pd.NaT], dtype="m8[ns]"))
 720 
 721         df1 = pd.DataFrame(["00:00:01"]).apply(pd.to_timedelta)
 722         df2 = pd.DataFrame(["00:00:02"]).apply(pd.to_timedelta)
 723         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 724             # Passing datetime64-dtype data to TimedeltaIndex is no longer
 725             #  supported GH#29794
 726             pd.DataFrame([pd.NaT]).apply(pd.to_timedelta)
 727 
 728         dfn = pd.DataFrame([pd.NaT.value]).apply(pd.to_timedelta)
 729 
 730         scalar1 = pd.to_timedelta("00:00:01")
 731         scalar2 = pd.to_timedelta("00:00:02")
 732         timedelta_NaT = pd.to_timedelta("NaT")
 733 
 734         actual = scalar1 + scalar1
 735         assert actual == scalar2
 736         actual = scalar2 - scalar1
 737         assert actual == scalar1
 738 
 739         actual = s1 + s1
 740         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, s2)
 741         actual = s2 - s1
 742         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, s1)
 743 
 744         actual = s1 + scalar1
 745         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, s2)
 746         actual = scalar1 + s1
 747         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, s2)
 748         actual = s2 - scalar1
 749         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, s1)
 750         actual = -scalar1 + s2
 751         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, s1)
 752 
 753         actual = s1 + timedelta_NaT
 754         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, sn)
 755         actual = timedelta_NaT + s1
 756         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, sn)
 757         actual = s1 - timedelta_NaT
 758         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, sn)
 759         actual = -timedelta_NaT + s1
 760         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, sn)
 761 
 762         msg = "unsupported operand type"
 763         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 764             s1 + np.nan
 765         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 766             np.nan + s1
 767         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 768             s1 - np.nan
 769         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 770             -np.nan + s1
 771 
 772         actual = s1 + pd.NaT
 773         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, sn)
 774         actual = s2 - pd.NaT
 775         tm.assert_series_equal(actual, sn)
 776 
 777         actual = s1 + df1
 778         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df2)
 779         actual = s2 - df1
 780         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df1)
 781         actual = df1 + s1
 782         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df2)
 783         actual = df2 - s1
 784         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df1)
 785 
 786         actual = df1 + df1
 787         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df2)
 788         actual = df2 - df1
 789         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df1)
 790 
 791         actual = df1 + scalar1
 792         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df2)
 793         actual = df2 - scalar1
 794         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, df1)
 795 
 796         actual = df1 + timedelta_NaT
 797         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, dfn)
 798         actual = df1 - timedelta_NaT
 799         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, dfn)
 800 
 801         msg = "cannot subtract a datelike from|unsupported operand type"
 802         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 803             df1 + np.nan
 804         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 805             df1 - np.nan
 806 
 807         actual = df1 + pd.NaT  # NaT is datetime, not timedelta
 808         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, dfn)
 809         actual = df1 - pd.NaT
 810         tm.assert_frame_equal(actual, dfn)

 812     # TODO: moved from tests.series.test_operators, needs splitting, cleanup,
 813     # de-duplication, box-parametrization...
 814     def test_operators_timedelta64(self):
 815         # series ops
 816         v1 = pd.date_range("2012-1-1", periods=3, freq="D")
 817         v2 = pd.date_range("2012-1-2", periods=3, freq="D")
 818         rs = Series(v2) - Series(v1)
 819         xp = Series(1e9 * 3600 * 24, rs.index).astype("int64").astype("timedelta64[ns]")
 820         tm.assert_series_equal(rs, xp)
 821         assert rs.dtype == "timedelta64[ns]"
 822 
 823         df = DataFrame(dict(A=v1))
 824         td = Series([timedelta(days=i) for i in range(3)])
 825         assert td.dtype == "timedelta64[ns]"
 826 
 827         # series on the rhs
 828         result = df["A"] - df["A"].shift()
 829         assert result.dtype == "timedelta64[ns]"
 830 
 831         result = df["A"] + td
 832         assert result.dtype == "M8[ns]"
 833 
 834         # scalar Timestamp on rhs
 835         maxa = df["A"].max()
 836         assert isinstance(maxa, Timestamp)
 837 
 838         resultb = df["A"] - df["A"].max()
 839         assert resultb.dtype == "timedelta64[ns]"
 840 
 841         # timestamp on lhs
 842         result = resultb + df["A"]
 843         values = [Timestamp("20111230"), Timestamp("20120101"), Timestamp("20120103")]
 844         expected = Series(values, name="A")
 845         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 846 
 847         # datetimes on rhs
 848         result = df["A"] - datetime(2001, 1, 1)
 849         expected = Series([timedelta(days=4017 + i) for i in range(3)], name="A")
 850         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 851         assert result.dtype == "m8[ns]"
 852 
 853         d = datetime(2001, 1, 1, 3, 4)
 854         resulta = df["A"] - d
 855         assert resulta.dtype == "m8[ns]"
 856 
 857         # roundtrip
 858         resultb = resulta + d
 859         tm.assert_series_equal(df["A"], resultb)
 860 
 861         # timedeltas on rhs
 862         td = timedelta(days=1)
 863         resulta = df["A"] + td
 864         resultb = resulta - td
 865         tm.assert_series_equal(resultb, df["A"])
 866         assert resultb.dtype == "M8[ns]"
 867 
 868         # roundtrip
 869         td = timedelta(minutes=5, seconds=3)
 870         resulta = df["A"] + td
 871         resultb = resulta - td
 872         tm.assert_series_equal(df["A"], resultb)
 873         assert resultb.dtype == "M8[ns]"
 874 
 875         # inplace
 876         value = rs[2] + np.timedelta64(timedelta(minutes=5, seconds=1))
 877         rs[2] += np.timedelta64(timedelta(minutes=5, seconds=1))
 878         assert rs[2] == value

 881         # GH 11349

 950

1395     def test_td64arr_with_offset_series(self, names, box_with_array):
1396         # GH#18849

1399 
1400         if box is pd.DataFrame:

1405             exname = names[1]

1407             exname = names[2]

1421             res2 = other + obj
1422         tm.assert_equal(res2, expected_add)
1423

1425         expected_sub = tm.box_expected(expected_sub, box2)

2034     def test_td64arr_mul_int_series(self, box_with_array, names, request):
2035         # GH#19042 test for correct name attachment
2036         box = box_with_array
2037         if box_with_array is pd.DataFrame and names[2] is None:
2038             reason = "broadcasts along wrong axis, but doesn't raise"
2039             request.node.add_marker(pytest.mark.xfail(reason=reason))

2041         exname = names[2] if box is not tm.to_array else names[1]

2044             ["0days", "1day", "2days", "3days", "4days"], name=names[0]

2051             dtype="timedelta64[ns]",

2060         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
2061

2063         result = ser.__rmul__(tdi)
2064         if box is pd.DataFrame:
2065             assert result is NotImplemented
2066         else:
2067             tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
